{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/agile-scrum-notes-09/","webpackCompilationHash":"29c01d4e109193ff99a0","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"zehengl","author":"Zeheng Li","siteUrl":"https://zehengl.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"491a4e1a-e1a6-59ec-85c0-630edbea6e02","excerpt":"Principles in monitoring Scrum Projects Ideally, the TEAM should monitor its own progress The manager or Scrum Master should NOT micro- manage The Scrum Master…","html":"<h2>Principles in monitoring Scrum Projects</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Ideally, the TEAM should monitor its own progress</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The manager or Scrum Master should NOT micro- manage</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Scrum Master should try to provide the team visibility so that they can make informed decisions</li>\n<li>\n<p>Common tracking mechanisms in Scrum</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Daily stand-up meetings</li>\n<li>Reviews and retrospectives</li>\n<li>Metrics</li>\n<li>Charts</li>\n<li>Information radiators</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Metrics</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A metric is a standard for measuring or evaluating something.</li>\n<li>\n<p>A measure is a quantity, a proportion, or a qualitative comparison of some kind.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Quantity: “There are 25 open defect reports on the application as of today.”</li>\n<li>Proportion: “This week there are 10 percent fewer open defect reports than last week.”</li>\n<li>Qualitative comparison: “The new version of the software is easier to use than the old version.”</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Types of metrics</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business</li>\n<li>RTF (Running Tested Features)</li>\n<li>Earned Business Value (EBV)</li>\n<li>Net Present Value (NPV)</li>\n<li>Internal Rate of Return (IRR)</li>\n<li>Return on Investment (ROI)</li>\n<li>Process</li>\n<li>Impediments cleared per iteration</li>\n<li>Impediments &#x26; User stories carried over the next iteration</li>\n<li>User stories done per iteration</li>\n<li>Defects carried over the next iteration</li>\n<li>Team member loading</li>\n<li>Velocity</li>\n<li>Backlog size</li>\n<li>Project Testing</li>\n<li>Acceptance tests per story</li>\n<li>Defects count per story</li>\n<li>Escaped Defects per cycle</li>\n<li>Tests time to run</li>\n<li>Tests run per frequency</li>\n<li>Time to fix tests</li>\n<li>Do’s and Don’ts</li>\n<li>Measure only a few things that matter (just because it can be measured doesn’t mean it is important)</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should be easy to calculate (ideally an automated process)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If it is too cumbersome, either people won’t do it or it will be incorrect</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>It should be easy to explain and interpret</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should result in tangible action</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Behavior that you want to encourage OR</li>\n<li>Behavior that you want to discourage</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Use metrics to guide action, not for witch-hunts</li>\n<li>In Scrum, team metrics are preferred</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do NOT use metrics for performance appraisals</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It will usually result in perverse incentive to manipulate the number</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Charts in Scrum</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Commonly used charts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Burn-down, Burn-up charts</li>\n<li>Cumulative Flow Diagrams</li>\n<li>Progress Charts</li>\n<li>Risk profile graphs</li>\n<li>Others</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Charts are useful because:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It indicates trends (trends are more important than absolute numbers)</li>\n<li>It is more “visual” (a picture is worth a thousand words)</li>\n<li>Management loves charts!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Burn-down Chart</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/8a209/burn-down-chart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 40.880503144654085%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"burn-down-chart\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/b9e4f/burn-down-chart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/cf440/burn-down-chart.png 148w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/d2d38/burn-down-chart.png 295w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/b9e4f/burn-down-chart.png 590w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/8a209/burn-down-chart.png 636w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Burn-down Chart Bar Style</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/7ec06/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 71.72131147540983%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"burn-down-chart-bar-style\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/b9e4f/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/cf440/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 148w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/d2d38/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 295w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/b9e4f/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 590w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/7ec06/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 732w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Burn-up and Burn-down Chart</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/e2ef7/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"burn-up-burn-down-chart\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/c739e/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/8ee9c/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 148w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/ebbe7/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 295w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/c739e/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 590w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/e2ef7/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 728w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Cumulative Flow Diagram</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/a111b/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.07692307692307%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"cumulative-flow-diagram\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/c739e/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/8ee9c/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 148w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/ebbe7/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 295w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/c739e/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 590w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/a111b/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 650w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Parking Lot Diagram</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/e49a9/parking-lot-diagram.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 69.21875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"parking-lot-diagram\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/b9e4f/parking-lot-diagram.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/cf440/parking-lot-diagram.png 148w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/d2d38/parking-lot-diagram.png 295w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/b9e4f/parking-lot-diagram.png 590w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/e49a9/parking-lot-diagram.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Escaped defects found</h2>\n<p>Escaped Defects Found counts number of new escaped defects found over period of time (day, week, month).</p>\n<h2>Velocity Chart</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/300a7/velocity-chart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 65.97014925373135%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"velocity-chart\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/b9e4f/velocity-chart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/cf440/velocity-chart.png 148w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/d2d38/velocity-chart.png 295w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/b9e4f/velocity-chart.png 590w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/f9b6a/velocity-chart.png 885w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/2d849/velocity-chart.png 1180w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/300a7/velocity-chart.png 1340w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Progress Chart / Kanban</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/fad88/kanban-board.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.26829268292683%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"kanban-board\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/b9e4f/kanban-board.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/cf440/kanban-board.png 148w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/d2d38/kanban-board.png 295w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/b9e4f/kanban-board.png 590w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/fad88/kanban-board.png 615w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Niko Niko Calendar</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/8ff1e/niko-niko-calendar.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 54%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"niko-niko-calendar\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/b9e4f/niko-niko-calendar.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/cf440/niko-niko-calendar.png 148w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/d2d38/niko-niko-calendar.png 295w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/b9e4f/niko-niko-calendar.png 590w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/8ff1e/niko-niko-calendar.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Information radiators</h2>\n<p>“An information radiator displays information in a place where passers by can see it. With information radiators, the passers by don’t need to ask any question; the information simply hits them as they pass.”</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Invented by Alistair Cockburn</li>\n<li>Team members can view the current state of the project : schedules, tasks, progress, issues</li>\n<li>Scrum teams should use it to make progress (or lack of) visible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/c0b12/information-radiators1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.26959247648903%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"information-radiators1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/c739e/information-radiators1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/8ee9c/information-radiators1.jpg 148w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/ebbe7/information-radiators1.jpg 295w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/c739e/information-radiators1.jpg 590w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/c0b12/information-radiators1.jpg 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Most popular Information radiators are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Task Boards</li>\n<li>Big Visible charts (Includes burn down charts)</li>\n<li>Continuous Integration build health Indicators (Including lava lamps and street lights)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/c0b12/information-radiators2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75.07836990595611%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"information-radiators2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/c739e/information-radiators2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/8ee9c/information-radiators2.jpg 148w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/ebbe7/information-radiators2.jpg 295w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/c739e/information-radiators2.jpg 590w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/c0b12/information-radiators2.jpg 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Effective Information Radiators should be :</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Simple</strong>: Should be Brief and concise.</li>\n<li><strong>Stark</strong>: Should display the progress and expose problems. Errors should not be masked, rather used to improve the work and performance</li>\n<li><strong>Current</strong>: Information displayed should be current</li>\n<li><strong>Transient</strong>: The problems and errors shouldn’t be there on the chart for long; once the problem has been rectified, it should be taken off</li>\n<li><strong>Influential</strong>: Influences the team members and management and empowers the whole team to take decisions</li>\n<li><strong>Highly</strong> visible</li>\n<li><strong>Minimal</strong> in number</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Agile Scrum Note 09: Monitoring Scrum Projects","date":"2016-01-28","description":"Tools and techniques to monitoring Scrum projects."}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-09/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-08/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Agile Scrum Note 08: Estimation"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-10/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Agile Scrum Note 10: Advanced Concepts"}}}}}